title: WiX — Learn How to Build Your Website with WiX
dec: Workshop format This workshop will be presented over 2 x 4-hr sessions and will be run via Zoom from 6pm to 10pm Sydney, Australia time. title: Space Data Hackers - June Meetup - SatGPT
dec: Do you want to learn how to use GPT and other powerful language models to simplify and enhance your Earth observation data analysis? Then don’t miss the June Space Data Hackers meetup, where Kevin Lalli will share his insights and experiences from working with cutting-edge optical systems for space, Earth, and metaverse applications. Kevin is currently the Payload Systems Lead at Hydrosat, a company that is building its own fleet of thermal imaging satellites. He has also worked on remote sensing projects for Planetary Resources, Bluefield Technologies, and Amazon Kuiper. Join us for an exciting and informative session with Kevin! Space Data Hackers is a community for people who love data and space. We explore datasets captured from space, share knowledge and build skills for putting data to use to solve problems for our communities, businesses and the world. We welcome all levels to join us for open discussion and talks from scheduled speakers about navigating data sets, machine learning, data analysis and cloud computing. Dive into space data with Space Data Hackers!
